./data/prayers/prayers_1527_Anon_2_R3: 5 -                    
                     Non nobis  domine non  non nobis /  / sed   nomini  tuo da  da gloriam.. A donai  domine  deus  magne rex ad rex ad mirabilis /  / qui  dedisti salutem in manus salutem in manus sancte virginis: per virtutem et per viscera dulcissime matris tue et y illud dulcissimum corpus tuum quod ex ea sumpsisti: exaudi preces meas et imple desiderium meum in bonu~. Et libera me ab omni tribulatione et angustia / et a morte subitanea / et ab omnibus insidijs / et ab omnibus michinocentibus / et a linguis iniquis et dolosis / et ab omnibus malis presentibus preteritis et futuris. Amen.
                  
                  	believed to be Language.LATIN

And when he  had sayd these thingis / one of the  bisshops ministers stondinge bye  gaue Iesus a blowe / sayng: Answerst  thou thus the Bisshop?

                   .xviij. Psalme.
               	believed to be Language.LATIN
./data/prayers/prayers_1536_Church_of_England_R2: 6 -                    THe heuyns declare the glorye  of god: And the fyrmament  manyfesteth the workes of  hys handes.                       7 -  Daye vnto daye vtteryth out 7 -  speache: and nyghte vnto nyghte 7 -  openyth knowledge. 7 -  There be neyther speaches nor 7 -  wordes: but that the voyces of the~ 7 -  byn harde. 7 -  Theyr sounde hathe gone thoroughe 7 -  all the worlde: and theyr 7 -  wordes throughe the costes of the 7 -  rounde earthe. 7 -  He hath pyght his pauilyon in ye
                     
                     7 -  sonne: & he is lyke a brydegrome 7 -  procedynge out of hys chambre. 7 -  He hath sterte vp lyke as a gyau~t 7 -  for to make hys course: hys commyng 7 -  forth is fro~ the hygh heuen. 7 -  And his recourse is vnto the furthest 7 -  parte therof: neyther is there 7 -  any man that can hyde hym from 7 -  hys heate. 7 -  The lawe of the lorde is pure, co~uertynge 7 -  soules: the testymonye of 7 -  the lorde is faythful geuyng wysedome 7 -  to the ignorant. 7 -  The co~maundementes of ye  lorde 7 -  be ryghtfull co~fortynge the herte: 7 -  the lordes precepte is clere gyuyng 7 -  lyght to the eyes. 7 -  The feare of the lorde is holye 7 -                       7 -                       8 -  euermore contynuynge: the iudgementes 8 -  of the lorde are true iustefyed 8 -  in them seluys. 8 -  They are to be desyred aboue golde 8 -  & precyous stone: & more swete 8 -  then hony / and the hony combe. 8 -  Verely thy seruaunte obserueth 8 -  them / in kepynge of them there is 8 -  greate rewarde. 8 -  Who dothe co~syder hys defautes? 8 -  purge me fro~ those that be secrete / 8 -  and fro~ other spare thy seruaunte. 8 -  If they haue nat the maystrye of 8 -  me: then shall I be clene, & shalbe 8 -  purgyd from the greattyst synne. 8 -  And the wordes of my mouthe 8 -  shalbe pleasaunt: and the medytacyon 8 -  of myne herte acceptable in 8 -  thy syght alwaye. 8 -  O lorde my helper: & my redemer.
                  
                  	believed to be Language.LATIN

./data/prayers/prayers_1536_Church_of_England_R2: 73 -                    UNto the haue I lyfte vp  myne eyes o god: whiche  inhabytest the heuens.  Euyn lyke as the eyes of seruau~tes  wayte: at the handes of theyr  maysters.  As the eyes of an hande mayden  be vpon her maystres: euen so be  our eyes vpon the lorde oure god,  vntyll he haue mercy vpon vs.  Haue mercye on vs, o lorde haue  mercye on vs: for we are fylled  with moche contemte.  For our soule is fylled very moche:  beynge scornyd of the ryche, &  despysed of the proude.
                  
                  	believed to be Language.LATIN

./data/prayers/prayers_1536_Church_of_England_R2: 74 -                    THey that truste in the lorde  as a mountayne of Syon:  he shall neuer more ben mouyd  whiche inhabyteth Ierusalem.  Mountaynes are in cyrcuyte of  it: and the lorde is in the cyrcuyte  of his people from this tyme forth  and euermore.                                             75 -  For god shall nat leue the rod of 75 -  synners vpon ye  lotte of the iuste: 75 -  lest the iuste shulde extende theyr 75 -  handes vnto synne. 75 -  Do well (o lorde) to the good and 75 -  vpryght in harte. 75 -  But those that swarue, the lorde 75 -  shall bryng in to bondes with the~ 75 -  that worke wyckednesse, & peace 75 -  ouer all Israell.

./data/prayers/prayers_1536_Church_of_England_R2: 91 -                    UNto the haue I lyfte vp  myne eyes o god: whiche  inhabytest the heuens.  Euyn lyke as ye eyes of  eyes of seruau~tes  wayte: at ye  ha~des of their maisters  As the eyes of an hande mayden  be vpon her maystres: euen so be  our eyes vpon the lorde oure god,  vntyll he haue mercy on vs.  Haue mercye on vs, o lorde haue  mercy on vs: for we are filled with  moche contemte.  For our soule is fylled verye moche:  beynge scornyd of the ryche, &  despysed of the proude.
                  
                  	believed to be Language.LATIN
